        <p class="govuk-body">Most funerals are arranged by the nearest relatives and if not by a close friend. If there is no one, the local or health authority will arrange a simple funeral.</p>
        <p class="govuk-body">The person may have left instructions about the type of funeral and burial they wanted. There is no legal obligation for these instructions to be followed, but they usually are.</p>
        <p class="govuk-body"><a class="govuk-link govuk-link" href="https://www.gov.uk/after-a-death/arrange-the-funeral?step-by-step-nav=4f1fe77d-f43b-4581-baf9-e2600e2a2b7a">Find out more about how to arrange a funeral</a></p>
